ACE2 is expected to be a drug target for cardiovascular diseases by reducing the content of vascular tension II and increasing the content of Ang (1-7) to contain the activity of the related vascular tension converter enzyme (Angiotensin-converting Enzyme, ACE). ACE2 is also the entry point for certain coronary viruses into cells.
