In addition, they published core technical norms used in the system.
Apple and Google state that the system is planned to be rolled out in three phases:
Introduction of tools to support governments in creating official coronary virus tracking applications that protect privacy
In order to integrate this function directly into the iOS and Andre systems, Google and Apple first launched the system through an operating system update, and subsequently removed the system in the same way as the threat of the epidemic, thus addressing the problem of follow-up monitoring.
